user.name: Karpagam Technology Business Incubator
user.description:
The Institute established a non-profit Trust for Technology Business Incubation Centre (TBI) in 2019 to oversee all activities pertaining to translating research and know-how developed in the Institute to the market place. TBI has three broad activities to achieve the above mandate: (i) Facilitating commercialization of R&D technologies, (ii) Promoting faculty to incubate start-up companies in collaborative mode and (iii) Facilitating alumni and local entrepreneurs to establish start-up venture.
TBI is supported by an advisory body consisting of industrialists, successful entrepreneurs, venture capitalists, and technical specialists. 

Incubation is open to all entrepreneurs (i.e., they need not be KAHE faculty, alumni or students) so long as the idea is innovative and has commercial feasibility. A comprehensive organizational ecosystem has been established by KAHE, with the TBI, to nurture innovation by established companies and start-ups in collaboration with faculty of KAHE. TBI, with a group of Angel Network and early stage Venture capital firms, is also the investing arm which can receive equity in the start-ups in lieu of the IP and Investment.
KAHE Technology Business Incubator

user.name: Nec Business Incubator
user.description: NEC Business Incubator, located near Kovilpatti in a rural area, is the only MSME approved Business Incubator covering 4 Southern Districts of Tamilnadu with an allocated buildup space of nearly 27,000 sq ft. We have a hi tech Rapid Prototyping lab facility, IoT lab and also house a fabrication lab. Based on our selection committee's recommendations, we promote and provide funding assistance to very early stage startups.

user.name: Deshpande Startups
user.description:
Deshpande Startups- India's Largest Incubation Center


Deshpande Startups of Deshpande foundation is a Section-8 “Technology Business Incubator” (TBI) which is also recognised by Dept. of Science and technology, Govt. of India. The objective is to promote Entrepreneurship in Non-metro, who aim to address the real problems and aspire to impact 1.1 billion lives living in non-metros in India.. Currently we have over 60 startups in our ecosystem and growing each day, Sandbox Startups prides in being a pioneer in nurturing ideas to shape up as startups and subsequently into successful businesses.


Our new premises is India’s Largest Incubator with over 100K Sq. Ft. premises with State-of-the-art facility, Makers & ESDM labs to build prototypes & products eventually from ideation phase. 

Our USP has been guiding startups to get clarity in their customer discovery process, segmenting them and connecting them with initial customers to validate their product/solution apart from providing networking opportunities with industry stalwarts, access to funds etc.

user.name: AIC-NMIMS Incubation Centre
user.description: AIC NMIMS Incubation Centre is launched by SVKM's NMIMS (Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies) in collaboration with the NITI Aayog, Government of India under the Atal Innovation Mission.
